===Etymology 1===
From late {{etyl|ang}} {{term|lagerce|lang=ang}}, from earlier {{term|lawerce|lang=ang}}, from a {{proto|Germanic|laiw(a)rikon}} (cognates include Dutch {{term|leeuwerik|lang=nl}}, German {{term|Lerche|lang=de}}), of unknown origin. Some Old English and Old Norse ({{term|lævirik|lang=non}}) forms suggest a compound meaning "treason-worker," but there is no preserved folk tale that ties into this theory.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# Any of various small, singing [[passerine]] [[bird]]s of the family ''[[Alaudidae]]''.
# Any of various resembling birds, usually ground-living, such as the [[meadowlark]] and [[titlark]]
# One who [[wake]]s early; one who is [[up with the larks]].

